sub_title: PhD student in quantum computing for condensed matter and chemistry bij Universiteit van Amsterdam
summary:
I am a PhD student in quantum computing for condensed matter and molecular systems at the University of Amsterdam, and a critical analytical thinker with a scientific, solution-oriented mindset.
I hold master's degrees in theretical physics and computer science from Leiden University. During my studies, I completed a 9-month internship in quantum computing at Volkswagen Group of America, San Francisco.
Besides topics related to quantum computing, I have a broad interest in other disciplines such as AI, economics, history, linguistics and geopolitics.
